                             @{b}NewEdit V1.16@{ub}

                       (c) 1992-1995 by  Uwe Roehm

Welcome to NewEdit, a very useful commodity that improves all string gadgets in the
system some new functions. Some more details are covered in the sections @{"Goal" link "Goal" 0} and
{"Functions" link "Functions" 0}.

   @{"Goal of the game   " link "Goal" 0}     What's this all about - in short.
   @{"Copyright          " link "Copyright" 0}     A must for every documentation.
   @{"Systemrequirements " link "Systemrequirements" 0}     NewEdit doesn't need much, but read on.
   @{"Installation       " link "Installation" 0}     No magic - installer script included ;-)
   @{"Programstart       " link "Startup" 0}     How to start NewEdit and how to get rid of it.
   @{"Configuration      " link "Configuration" 0}     There're some options
   @{"Functions available" link "Functions" 0}     READ THIS! PLEASE.
   @{"The Author         " link "Author" 0}     Me, I think.
   @{"His Credits        " link "Greetings" 0}     Huba!
