@endnode

@node "Goal" "Goal"
@next "Copyright"
@prev "Main"

 @{b}Goal@{ub}

NewEdit is a commodity that improves the functionality of each string gadget in the
system. Beside some @{"new edit functions" link "Functions" 0} NewEdit offers copy and paste of text between
the clipboard and string gadgets! And since version 1.16 there's also filename
completion possible.

Short:
  - Improves all string gadgets with
     - word for word movement and deletion,
     - changing between different string gadgets via cursor keys,
     - ESCape = cancel,
     - copy and paste between clipboard and string gadgets,
     - filename completion,
     - mathematical calculations,
     - insertion of date and time,
     - case toggling of characters and
     - in- and decresement od numbered file names.
  - Commodity
  - @{"Options" link "Configuration" 0} (Workbench and Shell)
  - Support for different keymaps
  - Support for locale.library
@endnode

@node "Copyright" "Copyright"
@next "Systemrequirements"
@prev "Goal"
 @{b}Copyright@{ub}

NewEdit is based on a program by Oliver Wagner (published on the german AmigaPlus
disk 9/92). The current version 1.16 is an enhancement of  NewEdit V1.6, that is
available on AmigaPlus disk 1/93.  NewEdit V1.16 is FreeWare!

There's also a second branch of NewEdit's development starting with V1.8, of which
Paul Huxham released several improved versions. To avoid any irritations I decided
to include all his functions and to follow his version numbers.
@endnode

@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Copyright"
 @{b}Systemrequirements@{ub}

NewEdit works on all Amiga computers with at least AmigaOS 2.04. Other languages are
supported starting with AmigaOS 2.1 (the locale.library is needed). For the
evaluation of mathematical expressions the »@{"calculus.library" link "Calculus" 0}« is used which can be
found e.g. on Aminet.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Startup"
@prev "Systemrequirements"
 @{b}Installation@{ub}

Copy NewEdit and its documentation into any directory you want. If you want to start
automatically at boot time I recommend to put it into »Sys:WBStartup/«. For the
evaluation function the »@{"calculus.library" link "Calculus" 0}« is needed in »libs:«, also NewEdit also
works without this library.

Since version 1.15 there's also an installer script which will do all the work for
you to install and even to configure NewEdit. Enjoy.
@endnode

@node "Startup" "Startup"
@next "Configuration"
@prev "Installation"
 @{b}Programstart and -end@{ub}

NewEdit can be launched from a shell or the workbench and installs its own global
stringhook instead of the original Intuition-hook. You can terminate it pressing
CONTROL-C or by starting NewEdit again.

As NewEdit 1.16 is a commodity, which is known by commodities.library, you can also
in-/activate it from within Commodore's ExChange program.
@endnode

@node "Configuration" "Configuration"
@next "Functions"
@prev "Startup"
 @{b}Configuration@{ub}

There are ten options available both for the start from a shell or from workbench
(as icon tooltypes):
 
  @{u}CLIPUNIT@{uu}  Specifies the unit of the clipboard used by NewEdit for the
            copy/paste operation. Default: 0.

  @{u}NOALT@{uu}     Tells NewEdit to ignore the right Alt key as qualifier for 
            commands (copy, paste, evaluate, date, time, case, filenumber).
            This is useful if some of the key combinations are already used
            by other tools.

  @{u}NOAMIGA@{uu}   Same as NOALT, but doen't use the right Amiga key as qualifier.

  @{u}NOCONTROL@{uu} Disables the commands which are introduced by the Control-key.

  @{u}NOESC@{uu}     Disables the exiting of string gadgets via the Escape-key.

  @{u}CALCKEY@{uu}   Specifies the character which starts the evaluation of the
            string gadget's contents as mathematical expression. Must
            be pressed together with the right Alt or right Amiga key
            which can not be altered.

  @{u}CASEKEY@{uu}   Specifies the character which toggles the case of the current
            character/word. Must be pressed together with the right Alt
            or right Amiga key which can not be altered.

  @{u}COUNTKEY@{uu}  Specifies the character which increases/decreases the count
            of a numbered file name. Must be pressed together with the 
            right Alt or right Amiga key which can not be altered.

  @{u}DATEKEY@{uu}   Specifies the character which inserts the current date into
            a string gadget. Must be pressed together with the 
            right Alt or right Amiga key which can not be altered.

  @{u}TIMEKEY@{uu}   Specifies the character which inserts the current time into
            a string gadget. Must be pressed together with the 
            right Alt or right Amiga key which can not be altered.
@endnode

@node "Functions" "Functions"
@next "Author"
@prev "Configuration"
 @{b}Functions@{ub}

@{u}Cursormovements@{uu}
   Alt Cursor Left        Move to start of previous word
   Alt Cursor Right       Move to start of next word
   Alt Backspace          Delete previous word
   Alt Delete             Delete next word
   Control a              Jump to start of line
   Control d              Delete current character
   Control e              Jump to end of line
   Control k              Delete upto end of line

@{u}Activation@{uu}
   Escape                 Synonym for RETURN Key         (accepting contents)
   Right Alt Cursor Up    Activate previous stringgadget (        -"-       )
   Right Alt Cursor Down  Activate next stringgadget     (        -"-       )

@{u}Clipboard@{uu}
   Right Alt or Amiga c   Copy text from stringgadgets into clipboard
   Right Alt or Amiga v   Insert text from clipboard at current cursorposition

@{u}Evaluation@{uu}
   Right Alt or Amiga e   Treats the string gadget's contents as mathematival
                          expression, evaluates it and replaces it with its 
                          result using the @{"calculus.library" link "Calculus" 0} (see below).

@{u}Filename-Completion@{uu}
   Alt TAB                Completes the current contents of a string gadget as a 
                          file name. The display blinks if this can't be done.
                          If multiple matches are possible NewEdit completes the
                          name upto the first differ and blinks. You can cycle
                          through the possible matches if you continue pressing 
                          Alt-TAB.

@{u}Time/Date@{uu}
   Right Alt or Amiga t   Insert actual time
   Right Alt or Amiga d   Insert current date

@{u}Case-Toggling@{uu}
   Right Alt or Amiga g   Toggle case of current character
   Shift right Alt g or   Toggle case until end of line or next non-alphabetic char
   Shift right Amiga g

@{u}Filenumbering@{uu}
   Right Alt or Amiga i   Increase number of a numbered filename by one
   Shift right Alt i or   Decrease filename's number by one
   Shift right Amiga i

@{u}All original edit functions remain the same:@{uu}
   Cursor Left            Move to previous character
   Cursor Right           Move to next character
   Shift Cursor Left      Move to start of line
   Shift Cursor Right     Move to end of line
   Delete                 Delete character under cursor
   Shift Delete           Delete until end of line
   Backspace              Delete character left of cursor
   Shift Backspace        Delete up to start of line
   Right Amiga Q          Undo
   Right Amiga X          Clear all
   Return or Enter        Accept contents and finish input
@endnode

